### parseScalarValue() {#a8f168615fb43a51a70c57eee12a86038}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>static StringRef parseScalarValue (<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> UnquotedValue, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; char &gt; &amp; Storage, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> LookupChars, <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/analysis/regionprinter-cpp/#aa37fbbce2360106772fd97ed06455d55">std::function</a>&lt; <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a>, <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/smallvectorimpl">SmallVectorImpl</a>&lt; char &gt; &amp;)&gt; UnescapeCallback)</>}
  labels = {["static"]}>
parseScalarValue - A common parsing routine for all flow scalar styles.

It handles line break characters by itself, adds regular content characters to the result, and forwards escaped sequences to the provided routine for the style-specific processing.


<ParametersList title="Parameters">
<ParametersListItem name="UnquotedValue">- An input value without quotation marks.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="Storage">- A storage for the result if the input value is multiline or contains escaped characters.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="LookupChars">- A set of special characters to search in the input string. Should include line break characters and the escape character specific for the processing scalar style, if any.</ParametersListItem>
<ParametersListItem name="UnescapeCallback">- This is called when the escape character is found in the input.</ParametersListItem>
</ParametersList>

<SectionUser title="Returns">
- The unfolded and unescaped value.
</SectionUser>

Definition at line <a href="#l02054">2054</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/support/yamlparser-cpp">YAMLParser.cpp</a>.
</MemberDefinition>

<Link id="l00191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="191"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">/// The Unicode scalar value of a UTF-8 minimal well-formed code unit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="192"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///        subsequence and the subsequence&#39;s length in code units (uint8&#95;t).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="193"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">///        A length of 0 represents an error.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="194" lineLink="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">using </span><span class="doxyHighlight"><a href="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500">UTF8Decoded</a> = std::pair&lt;uint32&#95;t, unsigned&gt;;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="195"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="196" lineLink="#aee2537a5e509713ca8ae26bef2ed947e"><span class="doxyHighlightKeyword">static</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="#a312eeacf9361f1c1516dbafdec94e500">UTF8Decoded</a> <a href="#aee2537a5e509713ca8ae26bef2ed947e">decodeUTF8</a>(<a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/stringref">StringRef</a> <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#a34bd74317e3f04bfc4318c2d1a470877">Range</a>) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00197" /><CodeLine lineNumber="197"><span class="doxyHighlight">  <a href="/docs/api/classes/anonymous-namespace-path-cpp-/stringref/#a20d37563688a61a452fb26e317e37308">StringRef::iterator</a> Position= <a href="/docs/api/files/lib/lib/target/lib/target/nvptx/nvvmintrrange-cpp/#a34bd74317e3f04bfc4318c2d1a470877">Range</a>.begin();</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00199" /><CodeLine lineNumber="199"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 byte: &#91;0x00, 0x7f&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00200" /><CodeLine lineNumber="200"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit pattern: 0xxxxxxx</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00201" /><CodeLine lineNumber="201"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Position &lt; End &amp;&amp; (&#42;Position &amp; 0x80) == 0) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00202" /><CodeLine lineNumber="202"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::make&#95;pair(&#42;Position, 1);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00203" /><CodeLine lineNumber="203"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00204" /><CodeLine lineNumber="204"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 bytes: &#91;0x80, 0x7ff&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00205" /><CodeLine lineNumber="205"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit pattern: 110xxxxx 10xxxxxx</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00206" /><CodeLine lineNumber="206"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Position + 1 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xE0) == 0xC0) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00207" /><CodeLine lineNumber="207"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00208" /><CodeLine lineNumber="208"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint32&#95;t codepoint = ((&#42;Position &amp; 0x1F) &lt;&lt; 6) |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00209" /><CodeLine lineNumber="209"><span class="doxyHighlight">                          (&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0x3F);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00210" /><CodeLine lineNumber="210"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (codepoint &gt;= 0x80)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00211" /><CodeLine lineNumber="211"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::make&#95;pair(codepoint, 2);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00212" /><CodeLine lineNumber="212"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00213" /><CodeLine lineNumber="213"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 3 bytes: &#91;0x8000, 0xffff&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00214" /><CodeLine lineNumber="214"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit pattern: 1110xxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00215" /><CodeLine lineNumber="215"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Position + 2 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xF0) == 0xE0) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00216" /><CodeLine lineNumber="216"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00217" /><CodeLine lineNumber="217"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00218" /><CodeLine lineNumber="218"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint32&#95;t codepoint = ((&#42;Position &amp; 0x0F) &lt;&lt; 12) |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00219" /><CodeLine lineNumber="219"><span class="doxyHighlight">                         ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0x3F) &lt;&lt; 6) |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00220" /><CodeLine lineNumber="220"><span class="doxyHighlight">                          (&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0x3F);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00221" /><CodeLine lineNumber="221"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Codepoints between 55296 and 57343 are invalid, as</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00222" /><CodeLine lineNumber="222"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// they are high / low surrogate halves used by UTF-16.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00223" /><CodeLine lineNumber="223"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (codepoint &gt;= 2048 &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00224" /><CodeLine lineNumber="224"><span class="doxyHighlight">        (codepoint &lt; 55296 || codepoint &gt; 0xDFFF))</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00225" /><CodeLine lineNumber="225"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::make&#95;pair(codepoint, 3);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00226" /><CodeLine lineNumber="226"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00227" /><CodeLine lineNumber="227"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 4 bytes: &#91;0x10000, 0x10FFFF&#93;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00228" /><CodeLine lineNumber="228"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// Bit pattern: 11110xxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx 10xxxxxx</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00229" /><CodeLine lineNumber="229"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (Position + 3 &lt; End &amp;&amp; ((&#42;Position &amp; 0xF8) == 0xF0) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00230" /><CodeLine lineNumber="230"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00231" /><CodeLine lineNumber="231"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80) &amp;&amp;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00232" /><CodeLine lineNumber="232"><span class="doxyHighlight">      ((&#42;(Position + 3) &amp; 0xC0) == 0x80)) &#123;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00233" /><CodeLine lineNumber="233"><span class="doxyHighlight">    uint32&#95;t codepoint = ((&#42;Position &amp; 0x07) &lt;&lt; 18) |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00234" /><CodeLine lineNumber="234"><span class="doxyHighlight">                         ((&#42;(Position + 1) &amp; 0x3F) &lt;&lt; 12) |</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00235" /><CodeLine lineNumber="235"><span class="doxyHighlight">                         ((&#42;(Position + 2) &amp; 0x3F) &lt;&lt; 6) |</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00237" /><CodeLine lineNumber="237"><span class="doxyHighlight">    </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">if</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> (codepoint &gt;= 65536 &amp;&amp; codepoint &lt;= 0x10FFFF)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00238" /><CodeLine lineNumber="238"><span class="doxyHighlight">      </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::make&#95;pair(codepoint, 4);</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00239" /><CodeLine lineNumber="239"><span class="doxyHighlight">  &#125;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00240" /><CodeLine lineNumber="240"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordFlow">return</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> std::make&#95;pair(0, 0);</span></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00302" /><CodeLine lineNumber="302"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The following functions are based on the gramar rules in the YAML spec. The</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00303" /><CodeLine lineNumber="303"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// style of the function names it meant to closely match how they are written</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00304" /><CodeLine lineNumber="304"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// in the spec. The number within the &#91;&#93; is the number of the grammar rule in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00305" /><CodeLine lineNumber="305"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// the spec.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00306" /><CodeLine lineNumber="306"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00307" /><CodeLine lineNumber="307"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// See 4.2 &#91;Production Naming Conventions&#93; for the meaning of the prefixes.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00308" /><CodeLine lineNumber="308"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00309" /><CodeLine lineNumber="309"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// c-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00310" /><CodeLine lineNumber="310"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production starting and ending with a special character.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00311" /><CodeLine lineNumber="311"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// b-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00312" /><CodeLine lineNumber="312"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production matching a single line break.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00313" /><CodeLine lineNumber="313"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// nb-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00314" /><CodeLine lineNumber="314"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production starting and ending with a non-break character.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00315" /><CodeLine lineNumber="315"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// s-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00316" /><CodeLine lineNumber="316"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production starting and ending with a white space character.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00317" /><CodeLine lineNumber="317"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// ns-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00318" /><CodeLine lineNumber="318"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production starting and ending with a non-space character.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00319" /><CodeLine lineNumber="319"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// l-</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00320" /><CodeLine lineNumber="320"><span class="doxyHighlight">  </span><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//   A production matching complete line(s).</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00321" /><CodeLine lineNumber="321"></CodeLine>

<Link id="l00325" /><CodeLine lineNumber="325"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">  ///                  | &#91;0xFF00-0xFFFD&#93; | &#91;0x10000-0x10FFFF&#93;</span></CodeLine>
